<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Chat1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Chat,</orth> subst., prate, in a good as well as bad sense: <cit><quote>leave this bootless c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 422" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 422</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>palmers' c. makes short their pilgrimage,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 791" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 791</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.266" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 266</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.284" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 284</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.270" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 270</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.65" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.63" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 63</bibl>. <cit><quote>To have some c.:</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 2.163" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 163</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.2.109" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 2, 109</bibl>. <cit><quote>let's hold more c.,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.228" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 228</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>